{"questionId":"19351","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Each athlete on a running team recorded the distance (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi></math> miles) they ran in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn></math> minutes.</p>\n<p>The median distance is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math> miles and the interquartile range is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></math> miles.</p>\n<p>This information is shown in the following box-and-whisker plot.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/366bb81efb0a690ef755154abfaf286274f9a5b6.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"color:#999;font-size:90%;font-style:italic;\">* This question is from an exam for a previous syllabus, and may contain minor differences in marking or structure.</p><p>valid approach&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg</em>&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1&nbsp; &nbsp;N2</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"19351","referenceCode":"20N.1.SL.TZ0.S_8a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the value of a.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]"